            <ObservedData>
              <Attribute Type="Description">In a 5-year-old by with mild Cornelia de Lange syndrome-4 (CDLS4; 614701), Dorval et al. (2020) identified a de novo heterozygous 4-bp deletion (c.943_946del, NM_006265) in exon 9 of the RAD21 gene, resulting in a frameshift and premature termination (Glu315GlnfsTer9). The mutation was identified by sequencing of a multigene panel containing 5 known CDLS genes and confirmed by Sanger sequencing. The mutation was not present in the ExAC and gnomAD databases. Functional studies were not performed.</Attribute>
